# CLAUDE.md

## Project Overview

This repository is part of the **FlyRank Frontend AI Engineering Internship**.

The purpose of this repository is to document the internship progress, maintain a professional Git workflow, and build frontend projects using AI-assisted development practices.

---

## AI Assistant Guidelines

When assisting with this project:

- Understand the existing code before making changes.
- Suggest production-quality solutions.
- Explain the reasoning behind important decisions.
- Prefer readability over clever implementations.
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies.
- Keep solutions simple unless complexity is required.

---

## Coding Standards

- Write clean, maintainable code.
- Use meaningful variable and function names.
- Keep files organized.
- Add comments only when they improve clarity.
- Follow consistent formatting.

---

## Git Commit Convention

Use Conventional Commits.

Examples:

- feat: add authentication page
- fix: resolve navbar layout issue
- docs: update README
- chore: add gitignore
- refactor: simplify component logic

---

## AI Workflow

Before accepting AI-generated code:

1. Review every change.
2. Verify correctness.
3. Test locally.
4. Commit only reviewed code.

AI should assist development—not replace engineering judgment.

---

## Documentation Rules

Keep documentation updated whenever:

- New features are added.
- Project structure changes.
- Setup instructions change.
- Development workflow changes.

---

## Goal

Build a professional, well-documented repository while following modern frontend engineering practices throughout the internship.